node.text: Sous la Coupole du Printemps 🌺#pianist #piano #classicalmusic #classicalmusician

This piece was one of two arabesques Debussy composed in his early years in 1891. These arabesques hint characteristics of Debussy's later impressionistic style. 
A beautiful piece, with two contrasting sections. It's beauty lies in it's simplicity amongst the chaos in this world.

🇬🇧I read an autobiography of king of classical music (Karl Böhm). Böhm said “Mozart is my guardian deity” This is a autobiography which about till the end of Richard Strauss. .

クラシック王(カールベーム)の伝記を読んでいます。ベームとモーツァルトについてベームはモーツァルトを自分の音楽の守護神と語っていました。これはリヒャルトシュトラウスの最後の人生までの自伝です。🇯🇵 .

Ich lese eine Autobiografie von dem König der klassische Musik (Karl Böhm). Böhm erzählte „Mozart ist meiner Schutzgott.“ Das ist eine Autobiografie, was bis dem letzt Leben von Richard Strauss.🇩🇪 .

node.text:
Super excited that my new classical guitar quartet suite "TWO LORDS" will be published in PATTERNS, out via Navona Records August 9th.💿
.
.
"TWO LORDS" is a three-movement piece composed for my thesis project when completing my M.Phil in @trinitycollegedublin.  It is inspired on the works of Fredrik Thordendal and Allan Holdsworth.  I composed, performed, and engineered the whole suite.  Outsourced the mastering to Grammy-award engineering legend Bob Katz.🎩
.
.
You can pre-order the CD (and check my many other social profiles) in the link in my bio. Follow me and stay up to date with all the news.  I produce music related content all the time. 😊
.
.

Note: Everyone having a little bit of composition knowledge, knows that writing for DB is damn hard if you’re not a DB player yourself. So I composed this with overview of composing for cello, but tuned in 4ths! Which now I think was wrong and I’ve already got an insight about writing for DB. Lovely Vanessa @littlebasslady joined me on this project in the very beginning of conceiving the main idea.
Vanessa, I appreciate your support and also playing the piece as it should be played! Thank you 😍
